==English==

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''limestone'''
# {{mineralogy}} An abundant [[rock]] of [[marine]] and fresh-water [[sediment]]s.  Primarily composed of [[calcite]].  Limestone occurs in a variety of forms, both [[crystal]]line and [[amorphous]].  

*Chemical composition: Calcium carbonate, <math>CaCO_3</math>
 
*Physical properties:
**Color: White, gray, pink, yellowish, brown to black 
**Luster: Usually earthy. Crystal planes may be reflective
**Fracture: Uneven

